The PV plants are located in 4 cities in Portugal (4 PVs are located in Lisbon; 1 is located in Setubal, Faro and Braga, respectively) and the available data vary from 14 to 30 months depending on the PV plant. The selected PV plants also differ in terms of nominal and peak capacities. The base PV has a nominal capacity of 23.52 KW, while the target domain PVs’ capacity varies from 30 KW to 271.53 KW, which is over 10 times the capacity of the base PV. The rationale behind the selection of the specific PV plants is to assess model performance on PV plants that are located both in the same city (PV2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
